-- Data migration: load the opening-day menu.
--
-- This is real content, not sample data, so it ships as a migration rather than
-- through `prisma/seed.mjs` (which is destructive and dev-only). `migrate deploy`
-- runs on every Vercel build, applies this exactly once, and never re-runs it —
-- so later edits made in /admin/menu are safe.
--
-- Ids are literal strings instead of cuids so the foreign keys resolve here in
-- plain SQL. `cuid()` is generated by Prisma Client, not by a column default, so
-- rows created later from the admin panel still get cuids. Both are just TEXT.
--
-- `updatedAt` is a Prisma client-side field: the column is NOT NULL with no
-- default, so a raw INSERT has to supply it.
--
-- Prices and descriptions start NULL — staff fill them in from /admin/menu.


